<br>
Go ahead, argue need, then evaluate alternatives against that need, as well as the other consequences of each proposed remedy.<br>
<br>
For example here, the best argument so far is that mages need an escape spell.  Root is proposed as a solution.  The counter argument is that root would make magicians too powerful.<br>
<br>
I have always been a strong advocate of improvements to the mage class when I thought there was a demonstrable need.  Recently, I supported, along with most mages, lifting the haste cap.  I have supported improvements and alternatives to frenzied burnout, which was definitely broken, but is only of dubious value.  I support cutting the refresh time on mend companion in half without making that a new AA.<br>
<br>
I have summarized and argued for improvements in the proposed PoP spell line for mages.<br>
<br>
In the past, I have successfully summarized the arguments in favor of stronger pets, neutral faction pets <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (which most mages thought would never see the light of day)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and eliminating the pet experience penalty, even when I disagreed with some of the particular proposals.<br>
<br>
I have been dedicated to the rational improvement of the mage class for quite some time.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, I am opposed to what I see as a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;shopping cart&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> approach to upgrading the mage class, i.e. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Oh, this looks nice!&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->  I want the mage class to retain its character, despite the blurring of classes.<br>
<br>
I am all for improvements which are reasonable remedies to actual needs.  I am against improvements simply for the sake of making mages more powerful than they already are.<br>
<br>
Reasonable people can disagree about what is needed.  Indeed, that is big part of this forum, to discuss what problems face the mage, and how best to solve them.<br>
<br>
But the burden on proof lies with those who ask for improvements, especially new capabilities.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Raz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
